The paper discusses the limitations of variational approaches based on neural networks for estimating mutual information, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper focuses on the bias-variance tradeoff and proposes a new estimator that reduces variance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
